			<section>
									<div class="summary">
						<p>A <code>Response</code> object is typically instantiated automatically by the <code>Controller</code>. It is assigned
any headers set in the course of the request, as well as any content rendered by the
<code>Controller</code>. Once completed, the <code>Controller</code> returns the <code>Response</code> object to the <code>Dispatcher</code>.</p>
					</div>
				
									<div class="description">
						<p>The <code>Response</code> object is responsible for writing its body content to output, and writing any
headers to the browser.</p>
					</div>
							</section>

			
			
			
